obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (30821)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30821&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the`
  line `Suppression of UnlawfulActs against Safety of Civil Aviation Act, 1982.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to thewhole of India and, save as otherwise provided in this Act, it applies also toany`
  line `offence under section 3 committed outside India by any person.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come intoforce on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification inthe`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 15th November 1982, vide notification No. S.O. 799(E), dated 12th November 1982, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30822)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1994, s. 2 (w.e.f. 19-9-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30822&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "aircraft" means any aircraft, whether or not registered in India, other than a military`
  line `aircraft or an aircraft used in customs or police service;`
  line
  line `(b) "aircraft registered in India" means an aircraft which is for the time being registered in`
  line India;
  line
  line `^1[(bb) "airport" means an aerodrome as defined in clause (2) of section 2 of the Aircraft Act,`
  line `1934 (22 of 1934);]`
  line
  line `(c) "Convention country" means a country in which the Montreal Convention is for the time`
  line `being in force;`
  line
  line `(d) "military aircraft" means an aircraft of the naval, military, air force or any other armed`
  line `forces of any country and includes every aircraft commanded for the time being by a person in`
  line `such force detailed for the purpose;`
  line
  line `(e) "Montreal Convention" means the Convention for the Suppression of Unlawful Acts`
  line `against the Safety of Civil Aviation signed at Montreal on the 23rd day of September, 1971.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) an aircraft shall be deemed to be in flight at any time from the moment when all its external`
  line `doors are closed following embarkation until the moment when any such door is opened for`
  line `disembarkation, and in the case of a forced landing, the flight shall be deemed to continue until the competent authorities of the country in which such forced landing takes place take over the`
  line `responsibility for the aircraft and for persons and property on board;`
  line
  line `(b) an aircraft shall be deemed to be in service from the beginning of the pre-flight preparation of`
  line `the aircraft by the ground staff or by the crew for a specific flight until twenty-four hours after any`
  line `landing and the period of such service shall include the entire period during which the aircraft is in`
  line flight.
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (30823)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Offence of committing violence on board an aircraft in flight, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30823&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever unlawfully`
  line `and intentionally--`
  line
  line `(a) commits an act of violence against a person on board an aircraft in flight which is likely to`
  line `endanger the safety of such aircraft; or`
  line
  line `(b) destroys an aircraft in service or causes damage to such aircraft in such a manner as to render`
  line `it incapable of flight or which is likely to endanger its safety in flight; or`
  line
  line `(c) places or causes to be placed on an aircraft in service, by any means whatsoever, a device or`
  line `substance which is likely to destroy that aircraft, or to cause damage to it which renders it incapable`
  line `of flight, or to cause damage to it which is likely to endanger its safety in flight; or`
  line
  line `(d) communicates such information which he knows to be false so as to endanger the safety of an`
  line `aircraft in flight,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for life and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever attempts to commit, or abets the commission of, any offence under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `also be deemed to be have committed such offence and shall be punished with the punishment provided`
  line `for such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (46652)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Offence at airport.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1994, s. 3 (w.e.f. 19-9-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=46652&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Offence at airport.-- (1) Whoever, at any airport, unlawfully and intentionally, using any`
  line `device, substance or weapon,--`
  line
  line `(a) commits an act of violence which is likely to cause grievous hurt or death of any person; or`
  line
  line `(b) destroys or seriously damages any aircraft or facility at an airport or disrupts any service at the`
  line airport,
  line
  line `endangering or threatening to endanger safety at that airport, shall be punished with imprisonment for life`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever attempts to commit, or abets the commission of, any offence under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `also be deemed to have committed such offence and shall be punished with the punishment provided for`
  line `such offence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (30824)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Destruction of, or damage to, air navigation facilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30824&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever unlawfully and`
  line `intentionally destroys or damages air navigation facilities or interferes with their operation in such a`
  line `manner as is likely to endanger the safety of the aircraft in flight shall be punished with imprisonment for`
  line `life and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever attempts to commit, or abets the commission of, any offence under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `also be deemed to have committed such offence and shall be punished with the punishment provided for`
  line `such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (30825)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30825&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), where an offence under section 3 is`
  line `committed outside India, the person committing such offence may be dealt with in respect thereof as if`
  line `such offence had been committed at any place within India at which he may be found.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under section 3 which is committed`
  line `outside India unless--`
  line
  line `(a) such offence is committed on board an aircraft registered in India;`
  line
  line `(b) such offence is committed on board an aircraft which is for the time being leased without`
  line `crew to a lessee who has his principal place of business, or where he has no such place of business,`
  line `his permanent residence in India; or`
  line
  line `(c) the alleged offender is a citizen of India or is on board the aircraft in relation to which such`
  line `offence is committed when it lands in India or is found in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (30826)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 7
  title `Conferment of powers of investigation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1994, s. 4 (w.e.f. 19-9-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30826&sectionno=5A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Conferment of powers of investigation, etc.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), for the purposes of this Act, the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, confer on any officer of the Central Government, powers of arrest,`
  line `investigation and prosecution exercisable by a police officer under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973.`
  line
  line `(2) All officers of police and all officers of Government are hereby required and empowered to assist`
  line `the officer of the Central Government referred to in sub-section (1), in the execution of the provisions of`
  line `this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (30827)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 8
  title `Designated Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1994, s. 4 (w.e.f. 19-9-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30827&sectionno=5B&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[5B. Designated Courts.-- (1) For the purpose of providing for speedy trial, the State Government`
  line `shall, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify a Court of Session to be a Designated Court for such area or areas as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), a`
  line `Designated Court shall, as far as practicable, hold the trial on a day-to-day basis.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_c:
  sectionId (30828)
  sectionNo 5C
  orderNo 9
  title `Offences triable by Designated Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1994, s. 4 (w.e.f. 19-9-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30828&sectionno=5C&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[5C. Offences triable by Designated Courts.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),--`
  line
  line `(a) all offences under this Act shall be triable only by the Designated Court specified under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5B;`
  line
  line `(b) where a person accused of or suspected of the commission of an offence under this Act is`
  line `forwarded to a Magistrate under sub-section (2) or sub-section (2A) of section 167 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), such Magistrate may authorise the detention of such person in`
  line `such custody as he thinks fit for a period not exceeding fifteen days in the whole where such`
  line `Magistrate is a Judicial Magistrate and seven days in the whole where such Magistrate is an`
  line `Executive Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such Magistrate considers,--`
  line
  line `(i) when such person is forwarded to him as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(ii) upon or at any time before the expiry of the period of detention authorised by him,`
  line
  line `that the detention of such person is unnecessary, he shall order such person to be forwarded to the`
  line `Designated Court having jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(c) the Designated Court may exercise, in relation to the person forwarded to it under clause (b),`
  line `the same power which a Magistrate having jurisdiction to try a case may exercise under section 167 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) in relation to an accused person in such case`
  line `who has been forwarded to him under that section;`
  line
  line `(d) a Designated Court may, upon a perusal of a complaint made by an officer of the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be, authorised in this behalf, take cognizance`
  line `of that offence without the accused being committed to it for trial.`
  line
  line `(2) When trying an offence under this Act, a Designated Court may also try an offence other than an`
  line `offence under this Act, with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), be charged at the same trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_d:
  sectionId (30829)
  sectionNo 5D
  orderNo 10
  title `Application of the Code to proceedings before a Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1994, s. 4 (w.e.f. 19-9-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30829&sectionno=5D&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[5D. Application of the Code to proceedings before a Designated Court.-- Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973(2 of 1974) shall apply to`
  line `the proceedings before a Designated Court and the person conducting a prosecution before a Designated`
  line `Court shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (30830)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 11
  title `Provisions as to extradition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30830&sectionno=6&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The offences under section 3 and section 4 shall be deemed to`
  line `have been included as extraditable offences and provided for in all the extradition treaties made by India`
  line `with Convention countries and which extend to, and are binding on, India on the date of commencement`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of the application of the Extradition Act, 1962 (34 of 1962) to offences under`
  line `this Act, any aircraft registered in a Convention country shall, at any time while that aircraft is in flight,`
  line `be deemed to be within the jurisdiction of that country, whether or not it is for the time being also within`
  line `the jurisdiction of any other country.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (30831)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 12
  title `Provision as to bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 19-9-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30831&sectionno=6A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Provision as to bail.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no person accused of an offence punishable under this Act shall, if in`
  line `custody, be released on bail or on his own bond unless`
  line
  line `(a) the Public Prosecutor has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such`
  line `release; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the court is satisfied that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not likely to`
  line `commit any offence while on bail.`
  line
  line `(2) The limitations on granting of bail specified in sub-section (1) are in addition to the limitations`
  line `under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law for the time being in force on`
  line `granting of bail.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the special powers of the High Court`
  line `regarding bail under section 439 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (30832)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 13
  title `Contracting parties to Convention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30832&sectionno=7&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, certify as to who are the contracting parties to the Montreal Convention and to what`
  line `extent they have availed themselves of the provisions of the Convention, and any such notification shall`
  line `be conclusive evidence of the matters certified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (30833)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to treat certain aircraft to be registered in Convention countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30833&sectionno=8&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `If the Central`
  line `Government is satisfied that the requirements of Article 9 of the Montreal Convention have been satisfied`
  line `in relation to any aircraft, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that such aircraft shall, for the purposes of this Act, be treated as registered in such Convention country as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (30834)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 15
  title `Previous sanction necessary for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30834&sectionno=9&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for an offence under this Act`
  line `shall be instituted except with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (30835)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 16
  title `Presumptions as to offences under sections 3, 3A and 4.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1994, s. 6 (w.e.f. 19-9-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30835&sectionno=9A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Presumptions as to offences under sections 3, 3A and 4.-- In a prosecution for an offence`
  line `under sections 3, 3A and 4, if it is proved--`
  line
  line `(a) that the arms, ammunition or explosives were recovered from the possession of the accused`
  line `and there is reason to believe that such arms, ammunition or explosives of similar nature were used in`
  line `the commission of such offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) that there is evidence of violence committed by the accused against any person in connection`
  line `with the commission of such offence,`
  line
  line `the Designated Court shall presume, unless the contrary is proved that the accused had committed such`
  line offence.]
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (30836)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 17
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893&sectionId=30836&sectionno=10&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00008_198266_1517807325893
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government for any damage caused`
  line `or likely to be caused for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
